===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|lībrātiō||a hurling, swinging}}, from {{m|la|lībrō||poise, cause to swing}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK|US}} {{IPA|en|/laɪˈbɹeɪ.ʃən/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-libration.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The act of [[librate|librating]].
# {{lb|en|astronomy}} The [[apparent]] [[wobble]] or [[variation]] in the [[visible]] side of the [[Moon]] that [[permanently]] faces the [[Earth]], allowing [[observer]]s on Earth to see, over a period of time, [[slightly]] more than [[half]] of the [[lunar]] [[surface]].
# {{lb|en|by extension}} A similar [[rotational]] or [[orbital]] characteristic of some other [[celestial]] body.
# {{lb|en|[[dynamics]]}} The [[oscillation]] of an [[angle]] about a [[stable equilibrium]] point<ref>{{cite web |first=Alessandro |last=Morbidelli |date=2002 |url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Modern-celestial-mechanics-%3A-aspects-of-solar-Morbidelli/05a1b074f5d84e53f88497adeac003e94cd7427f |work=Modern celestial mechanics: aspects of solar system dynamics |page=73}}</ref>.
# {{lb|en|chemistry}} A vibrational degree of freedom whereby a group of atoms partly rotates back and forth, similar to the Moon's motion.

